      <abstract>
        <p>June 1 article about Robert B Zoellick, Pres Bush's nominee to be next president of World Bank, gave incorrect figure for bank's total lending to poor countries; it is $23 billion</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article yesterday about Robert B. Zoellick, President Bush's nominee to be the next president of the World Bank, gave an incorrect figure in some copies for the bank's total lending to poor countries. It is $23 billion, not $23 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article yesterday about Robert B. Zoellick, President Bush's nominee to be the next president of the World Bank, gave an incorrect figure in some copies for the bank's total lending to poor countries. It is $23 billion, not $23 million.</p>
      </block>
